John Edward: Language skills are important for global citizens
Scottish private schools have remained at the top of the Academic Excellence Rankings and continued in 2018 with the following outstanding exam results, reinforced by personal and collective success in sports, art, music and other community activities.
These schools, with over 30,000 pupils all over Scotland and represented by the Scottish Council for Private Schools (SCIS), strive to provide the best service to their pupils and their parents.
Private schools aim to prepare students for further and higher education, their chosen profession, and their place as world citizens.
